<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,402,643]" pageId="8" pageNumber="515">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,510,535]" pageId="8" pageNumber="515">Description.</emphasis>
Body broadly oval, copperish brown with dark brown to black punctures. Head and anterior margin of pronotum darker than the remaining dorsal surface; lateral margin of mandibular plates, anterior and anterolateral margins of pronotum, and anterior half of the lateral margin of coria lined in black. Body surface bearing sparse, short setae densely distributed on abdominal venter.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322289/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="515" targetBox="[166,1401,702,1853]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1435,1897,1950]" pageId="8" pageNumber="515">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,1897,1919]" pageId="8" pageNumber="515">FIGURE 7.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[281,543,1897,1919]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Ocellatocoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="515" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longirostris" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[281,543,1897,1919]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="515">Ocellatocoris longirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[549,630,1898,1919]" pageId="8" pageNumber="515" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[549,630,1898,1919]" pageId="8" pageNumber="515">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, male holotype, A–C, dorsal, ventral and lateral view respectively. D, head and pronotum, dorsal. Scale bars = 1mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322290/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="516" targetBox="[151,1436,193,1245]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1276,1389]" pageId="9" pageNumber="516">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,277,1276,1298]" pageId="9" pageNumber="516">FIGURE 8.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[286,551,1276,1298]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Ocellatocoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longirostris" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[286,551,1276,1298]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="516">Ocellatocoris longirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[559,642,1276,1297]" pageId="9" pageNumber="516" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[559,642,1276,1297]" pageId="9" pageNumber="516">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, male holotype, pygophore, A–D, dorsal, ventral, posterior and lateral view respectively. E–G, dorsal, ventral and posterior view respectively. Abbreviations: dr, dorsal rim; il, inferior layer of ventral rim; p1, projection 1; p2, projection 2; p3, projection 3; pa, posterolateral angle; par, parameres; sl, superior layer of ventral rim; X, segment X. Scale bars = 0.5mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1434,2035]" pageId="9" pageNumber="516">
Head declivous, slightly longer than wide; lateral margins of mandibular plates sinuous and slightly elevated, without projections before the eyes. Mandibular plates and clypeus subequal in length, round at apex. Middle of clypeus tumescent. Ocelli small, the diameter of each ocellus less than twice the diameter of one puncture. Ocelli placed behind an imaginary line connecting the posterior limit of eyes (
<figureCitation box="[953,1019,1542,1567]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1897,1919]" captionTargetBox="[166,1401,702,1853]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[166,1421,695,1875]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Ocellatocoris longirostris sp. nov., male holotype, A – C, dorsal, ventral and lateral view respectively. D, head and pronotum, dorsal. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322289/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="516">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
A, D); interocellar distance about 4.5 times the distance between each ocellus and the nearest eye. Eyes small, width of each eye less than? the width of head across the eyes. Antennae brown; antennal tubercles not visible in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[1119,1188,1614,1639]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1897,1919]" captionTargetBox="[166,1401,702,1853]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[166,1421,695,1875]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Ocellatocoris longirostris sp. nov., male holotype, A – C, dorsal, ventral and lateral view respectively. D, head and pronotum, dorsal. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322289/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="516">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
A). Bucculae rounded anteriorly, evanescent posteriorly attaining the base of head. Labium light brown; first segment reaching prosternum, second segment slightly surpassing mesocoxae, third surpassing urosternite III, and the fourth segment attaining urosternite VI.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1434,2035]" pageId="9" pageNumber="516">Pronotum irregularly punctured, transversally striated; cicatrices conspicuous, slightly tumescent. Anterolateral margins almost straight; anterior half of anterolateral margins crenulate; anterolateral angles projected laterad of eyes by half the width of one eye. Humeral angles rounded. Scutellum almost 1.2 times longer than wide at base, attaining the level of middle of connexivum V; apex broadly rounded. Frenal and postfrenal portions of scutellum subequal in length. Punctures denser than on pronotum, and smaller and denser near the apical margin of scutellum; black fovea present in basal angles. Hemelytra regularly punctured; punctures denser than on scutellum; apex of each corium setose. Trocanthers and base of femora light brown, tibiae and tarsi dark brown; tibiae with dorsal, shallow sulcus.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="10" pageNumber="517">Connexivum exposed, dark brown, bearing shallow punctures and short setae. Posterolateral angles of urosternites round. Ventral abdomen copperish, densely setose except at middle of sternites III to VI. Urosternites III to V longitudinally depressed at midline. Trichobothria lateral of imaginary line tangent to lateral margins of spiracles IV to VI.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="10" pageNumber="517">
Male genitalia. Pygophore globose; posterolateral angles poorly developed, broadly rounded (
<figureCitation box="[1258,1324,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1276,1298]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1245]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1254]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ocellatocoris longirostris sp. nov., male holotype, pygophore, A – D, dorsal, ventral, posterior and lateral view respectively. E – G, dorsal, ventral and posterior view respectively. Abbreviations: dr, dorsal rim; il, inferior layer of ventral rim; p 1, projection 1; p 2, projection 2; p 3, projection 3; pa, posterolateral angle; par, parameres; sl, superior layer of ventral rim; X, segment X. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322290/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="517">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
A, B, pa). Dorsal rim concave, bearing 1+1 short projections near base of segment X (
<figureCitation box="[1015,1082,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1276,1298]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1245]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1254]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ocellatocoris longirostris sp. nov., male holotype, pygophore, A – D, dorsal, ventral, posterior and lateral view respectively. E – G, dorsal, ventral and posterior view respectively. Abbreviations: dr, dorsal rim; il, inferior layer of ventral rim; p 1, projection 1; p 2, projection 2; p 3, projection 3; pa, posterolateral angle; par, parameres; sl, superior layer of ventral rim; X, segment X. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322290/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="517">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
A, C, D, dr, p1), and 1+1 long, laminar projections lateral to segment X (fig 8A,C, D, p2). Inferior layer of ventral rim broadly concave (
<figureCitation box="[1343,1410,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1276,1298]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1245]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1254]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ocellatocoris longirostris sp. nov., male holotype, pygophore, A – D, dorsal, ventral, posterior and lateral view respectively. E – G, dorsal, ventral and posterior view respectively. Abbreviations: dr, dorsal rim; il, inferior layer of ventral rim; p 1, projection 1; p 2, projection 2; p 3, projection 3; pa, posterolateral angle; par, parameres; sl, superior layer of ventral rim; X, segment X. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322290/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="517">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
B, vr, il); superior layer of ventral rim with 1+1 large laminate projections lateral to segment X, partially covering the parameres both in posterior and in dorsal views (
<figureCitation box="[706,774,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1276,1298]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1245]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1254]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ocellatocoris longirostris sp. nov., male holotype, pygophore, A – D, dorsal, ventral, posterior and lateral view respectively. E – G, dorsal, ventral and posterior view respectively. Abbreviations: dr, dorsal rim; il, inferior layer of ventral rim; p 1, projection 1; p 2, projection 2; p 3, projection 3; pa, posterolateral angle; par, parameres; sl, superior layer of ventral rim; X, segment X. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322290/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="517">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
A–G, vr, sl, p3). Parameres long and falciform, projecting anterolaterally lateral to segment X and curving about 90° posterolaterally over the laminate projections of the dorsal rim (
<figureCitation box="[280,347,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1276,1298]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1245]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1254]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ocellatocoris longirostris sp. nov., male holotype, pygophore, A – D, dorsal, ventral, posterior and lateral view respectively. E – G, dorsal, ventral and posterior view respectively. Abbreviations: dr, dorsal rim; il, inferior layer of ventral rim; p 1, projection 1; p 2, projection 2; p 3, projection 3; pa, posterolateral angle; par, parameres; sl, superior layer of ventral rim; X, segment X. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322290/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="517">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
A–G, par). Segment X broad, membranous at basal ¾, emarginate at apex (
<figureCitation box="[1193,1259,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1276,1298]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1245]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1254]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ocellatocoris longirostris sp. nov., male holotype, pygophore, A – D, dorsal, ventral, posterior and lateral view respectively. E – G, dorsal, ventral and posterior view respectively. Abbreviations: dr, dorsal rim; il, inferior layer of ventral rim; p 1, projection 1; p 2, projection 2; p 3, projection 3; pa, posterolateral angle; par, parameres; sl, superior layer of ventral rim; X, segment X. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322290/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="517">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
A–G, X).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="10" pageNumber="517">
